---
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
---

<section class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
  <div class="container">
    <div
      class="rounded-2xl bg-accent-lighter/50 p-8 md:gap-x-12 md:px-16 md:py-12 lg:px-20 lg:py-16"
    >
      <!-- What is Carmen? -->
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl text-center">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl">
          What is
          <span class="font-bold text-primary">Carmen?</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl">
          Carmen (Carbon Measurement Engine) is an open-source tool that measures the carbon footprint of cloud-based software at two critical levels. Built by Amadeus engineers and contributed to the Green Software Foundation, Carmen provides accurate, actionable data to help organizations understand and reduce their cloud computing environmental impact.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl">
          At the infrastructure level, Carmen monitors energy consumption and emissions from virtual machines and cloud services. At the application level, it tracks the carbon footprint of individual Kubernetes pods and workloads. By integrating with your existing Prometheus monitoring and leveraging the Impact Framework, Carmen transforms complex metrics into clear carbon emissions dataâ€”enabling you to identify high-carbon workloads, optimize resource allocation, and track sustainability improvements over time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Validation Banner -->
      <div class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white py-4 shadow-sm md:mt-12">
        <div class="animate-marquee whitespace-nowrap text-lg font-medium text-primary">
          <span class="mx-4">Open Source & MIT Licensed</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">Developed by Amadeus Engineers</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">Built on Impact Framework</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">GSF Project</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">Open Source & MIT Licensed</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">Developed by Amadeus Engineers</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">Built on Impact Framework</span> |
          <span class="mx-4">GSF Project</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
